        ]
      ],
      "content": "Salt-crusted timbers stretch over murky water. Ropes creak against iron cleats as a handful of small boats rock in the swell. A painted sign nailed to a post reads: **HARBOUR GATE — NORTH**. Beyond the gate lies the marina, but passage isn't free."
    },
